Hiya, Japanese studying pervert here. On page 31, the text bubble where she says, "It's getting dark", in Japanese reads, "暗くなっちゃう". This can be translated as, It'll get dark or It's getting dark (lit. It gets dark).  This is due to the fact that the dictionary form of a verb acts as both present and future. Given the surrounding context I believe the former translation is a better fit, as she references the time of day in the previous bubble with the shota still going at it. It is unlikely that she can actually see.
